@ carolineistanbu @ sproteen @ peace_love8294 @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent for poorly understood conditions , i ’ ve found “ super science-y patient experimentalists ” to be the most useful source of practical advice . @ lateafternoon_k @ farid__jalali @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent you might also take a look at this talk : https : //t.co/e7u1gjw0dc @ lateafternoon_k @ farid__jalali @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent that ’ s interesting re : viral protein hiding out in connective tissue ( especially tissue types with low blood flow ) . it might help to explain the intense mast cell activation many w/ long covid experience . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent but honestly , a lot of chronic illnesses have fallen into the same trap . that is a big reason so many of them are chronic . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent i think the hardest thing about all this for me is that i thought if it happened at scale , if it were faster and less invisible , we would be smarter . i am seeing zero evidence that we are . @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent definitely not either or . and i am sure microclots are explicable , just like every other finding . it ’ s just when people find something , they jump to quickly to * cause * or “ biomarker. ” @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent i see a lot of people saying lc is an endothelial/vascular disease . i am sure that was a lot of the logic for housing it under cv @ nih , rather than niaids . @ ahandvanish @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent i am well aware of the research . i am saying on that we should take care to jump from a finding to using it to classify a disease or equate that finding with either biomarker or cause . ( we have and will find a lot of dysfunction ! ) @ ahandvanish @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent there are some conditions that have fairly straightforward pathology and cause . this is probably not one of them . i concerned about lc being classed as an endothelial disease for the same reason i am concerned about pots classed an autoimmune disease . or me a metabolic disease . @ carolineistanbu @ sproteen @ peace_love8294 @ microbeminded2 @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent “ top people , ” in my experience , are often latecomers . they have consistently been the least useful sources of medical advice or care throughout my ten year health odyssey . ( not recommending this protocol , just saying ) @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent also # whynotboth ? i am sure there are people with major damage and persistent infection . both could drive ongoing inflammation , ongoing damage/failure to repair , and altered immune response . hmm this sounds familiar . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent one of my big concerns is how excited people are about the microclot findings . i am concerned that if we don ’ t approach this with the wisdom that 1 ) this is a heterogenous population 2 ) many people who don ’ t recover may have multiple things wrong with them @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent we ’ ve given up on prevention . there is no other reason not to be officially counting duration of cases . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent the historical piece here that undergirds some of my concerns about how this will play out are the outbreaks in the 80s of a ( still unidentified virus ) that caused ebv reactivation , just like we are seeing in long covid patients . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent 3 ) people will require bespoke intervention , we will fail at both treatment trials and treatment . outpatient medicine can ’ t handle more than one variable . most will fail to diagnose patients with multiple pathologies , unless obvious on testing . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent good luck finding the “ cause ” ’ of # longcovid , truly . ( although agree that eliminating persistent infection may be biggest common denominator . ) @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent when this turned out not to be an explanatory factor , there was backlash ( from official scientists , ie people working at cdc/nih ) that led to a general media backlash against these patients ( “ yuppie flu ” ) . history can make us wise or we can choose to be foolish . @ danaparish @ nih @ us_fda @ who @ whcovidresponse @ joebiden @ cdcdirector @ microbeminded2 @ farid__jalali @ marybethpf @ pierrekory @ stevephillipsmd @ dianaberrent a lot of the early long covid findings are things one would expect to find in someone with a post-acute infectious , inflammatory condition . and doctors hate “ non-specific findings. ” meanwhile , we will keep looking at the average treatment effect level , so that ’ s what we will find
