 in history . beyond that – he ’ ll restore a sense of decency & amp ; goodness that is sorely missing from the presidency today . i 'm committed to ensuring the biden white house looks like this on june 26th , 2021. https : //t.co/kgtywrqpjb there were serious political risks to endorsing marriage equality in 2012 . a lot of people thought it would weaken obama & amp ; biden 's chances for reelection . but @ joebiden cared more about doing what was right than what some polls suggested he should do . https : //t.co/lektdpnuzk . @ joebiden called me the day of the scotus marriage equality ruling 5 years ago today . you would have thought it was his own wedding day he was so joyous . but that ’ s the thing about biden – he cares so deeply & amp ; sees the humanity in all people . it 's what makes him a great leader . seated on a stool in the packed living room , @ joebiden did what he does best . he listened , he thought , and he spoke from the heart . “ all you ’ ve got to do is look in the eyes of those kids , ” the vp said . “ no one can wonder whether they are cared for and nurtured and loved. ” . @ joebiden continued : “ it ’ s going to become a political liability in the near term for someone to say , ‘ i oppose gay marriage. ’ mark my words . and my job — our job — is to keep this momentum rolling to the inevitable. ” for me , however , @ joebiden ’ s marriage equality endorsement was somewhat less of a surprise . two weeks earlier , the vice president had made similar comments to me and a small group of lgbtq obama campaign supporters in los angeles . https : //t.co/ejnb4zwkes with the issue of marriage front & amp ; center for so many americans , i asked @ joebiden where he stood . “ when you came in tonight , you met michael & amp ; sonny ( our hosts ) and their two kids . and i wonder if you can talk about your own personal views as it relates to # marriageequality. ” which is why it sent shockwaves throughout america when vice president @ joebiden , in a s